  "text": "In text instance level methods [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] , [CITATION_5] , [CITATION_6] , [CITATION_7] , [CITATION_8] , [CITATION_9] , [CITATION_10] , detection of text follows the standard routine of general object detection, where a regionproposal network and a refinement network are combined to make predictions. The region-proposal network produces initial and coarse guess for the localization of possible text instance, and then a refinement part discriminates the proposals as text/non-text and also correct the localization of the text.",
